@node INTRO "Online2 what???? So, what the hell is it?"

     Right here it is:

     A program to convert .log files created by Online O'Meter (written by
Ellis Prichard) to Netstat (written by Tom Miles) .log files.

     Why? Well, I used to use Netstat and liked the Netanalyser program it
came with. This shows a number of useful statistics based on the time you
spend online. However, I found that the main netstat program was a little
buggy and the interface wasnt font sensitive etc. Therefore, I decided to
use Online O'Meter instead. This meant that I couldnt use the Netanalyser
program anymore..

    Then one evening I thought; "Hey, I bet I could write a program to
convert the Online O'Meter logfile to a Netstat one in Arexx". Two hours
later and 'bingo', Online2Netstat was born...

@endnode

