@endnode

@node REQUIRE "What ya need.." 
@{fg highlight}Online2Netstat needs:@{fg text} 
----------------	

RexxMast ( The Arexx interpreter running )

(and thus:)

OS2.0+

@endnode

@node USAGE "How do I use it then?"

     To  use  Online2Netstat  you must have the AREXX interpreter; REXXMAST
running.   If  it isnt run on startup you can run it from the CLI like
this:

@{fg fill}RexxMast >nil:@{fg text}

     If  you  want it to be run everytime you boot up, place the above
line  in  the  s:user-startup  file  or s:startup-sequence.  You could
instead  simply  drag  the RexxMast icon from sys:system drawer to the
sys:WBStartup drawer which would have the same effect.

	Heres the template for Online2Netstat:

@{fg highlight}Online2Netstat OnlineFile/A NetstatFile/A@{fg text}

OnlineFile  = Online O'Meter .log file
NetstatFile = destination Netstat .log file  

@(b}NOTE:@{ub}

   For the moment the CLI parsing is very basic. So, you have to put the
names of the two files in the exact order as above, WITHOUT the keywords.
This may be fixed in a later version.

@endnode

@node FEATURES "Online in -> Netstat out..Simple.. :)"
@{fg highlight}Features:@{fg text}

- Converts Online O'Meter .log files to Netstat ones, thus allowing you to
use them with the useful Netanalyser package that come with Netstat.

@endnode

@node BUGS "Arhhhhh no not them....!"
@{b}KNOWN BUGS@{ub}
----------

So far, so good - I.E no bugs. Although I have not tested the program with
an Online O'Meter .log file containing a single call which costs over
10UKP. If you have gone crazy and been online for such a long time, the
conversion may fail.

If you discover ANY other bugs that occur during use, please report them to
@{"me" link CONTACT} as soon as possible.  I will then attempt to fix them, and mail you the
new version.

@endnode

@node HISTORY "What has been changed and added.."
@{fg highlight}Online2Netstat Version History@{fg text}
-------------------------

V1.0 - 14/9/97: ( RELEASED ONTO AMINET: 15/09/97)

- First version. Simply converts the Online O'Meter .log file, nothing
else.

@endnode

@node TODO "What next then?"

Hmmm...Possibly add a switch which lets you segment your Online O'Meter
.log file into different sections. Basically, you'll place an extra field
in the .log file (I.E PC to state that the call was made on the PC, not the
Amiga - I do this!) and Online2Netstat will create two Netstat log files:
one for Amiga calls, one for PC ones......

    If  you have any ideas or find some bugs ( I hope not!  ), feel free to
@{"mail em to me!" link CONTACT}

@endnode

